title: Cross-Process Access OpenProcess to LSASS
id: 9a3e214d-fa32-4712-a108-11ef842cc7bc
status: stable
description: Detects anomalous applications opening handles to LSASS with specific memory access masks indicative of process injection or credential dumping attempts.
author: Detection Engineer Specialist
date: 2026/06/28
tags:
    - attack.defense_evasion
    - attack.privilege_escalation
    - attack.t1055
logsource:
    product: windows
    category: process_access
detection:
    selection:
        TargetImage|endswith: '\lsass.exe'
        GrantedAccess:
            - '0x1F0FFF' # PROCESS_ALL_ACCESS
            - '0x1010'   # PROCESS_VM_READ | PROCESS_QUERY_INFORMATION
            - '0x1410'   # PROCESS_VM_READ | PROCESS_QUERY_INFORMATION | PROCESS_QUERY_LIMITED_INFORMATION
    filter_legitimate:
        SourceImage|endswith:
            - '\msmpeng.exe'
            - '\svchost.exe'
    condition: selection and not filter_legitimate
falsepositives:
    - Local antivirus or EDR agents conducting legitimate security verification scan loops.
level: critical